{"lemma":"ساقِطَةٍ","slug":"ساقِطَةٍ","root":"س.ق.ط","root_slug":"س-ق-ط","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ق-ط","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n20076","n20097"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D8%A7%D9%82%D9%90%D8%B7%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"prostitute, whore, harlot"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the feminine active participle of سَقَطَ (saqaṭa, “to fall, to drop, to descend”). سَاقِط (sāqiṭ) + ـَة (-a)."},"ipa":["/saː.qi.tˤa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n20076","headword_ar":"ساقطهُ","root":"sqT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musaAqaTapN","text_ar":"مُسَاقَطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siqaATN","text_ar":"سِقَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asoqaTahu","text_ar":"اَسْقَطَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he made it to fall, fall down, drop, drop down,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tumble down, in consecutive portions"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quantities;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAbaEa A_isoqaATahu","text_ar":"تَابَعَ اـِسْقَاطَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AasoqATahu","text_ar":"اَسْقاطَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (M, K:) or it has both of these significations. (So in the L, and in some copies of the S; but in one copy of the S, the former only is mentioned.) A poet says, (S, M,) namely Dábi Ibn-El-Hárith ElBurjumee, (TA,) describing a [wild] bull and the dogs, (S,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"yusaAqiTu Eanohu rawoquhu DaAri yaAtihaA\n                      \n                     \n                        siqaATa Hadiydi Alqayoni A^axowala A^axowalaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His horn makes to fall consecutively from him those of them that were trained for hunting, as the iron of the blacksmith makes"},{"kind":"text","text":"sparks"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to fall consecutively, scattered about"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, M.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sAqT","text_ar":"ساقط"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxayola","text_ar":"الخَيْلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a horse)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"outstripped the"},{"kind":"text","text":"[other]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"horses:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [as though he made them to drop behind him, one after another.] ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sAqThu AlHadiyva","text_ar":"ساقطهُ الحَدِيثَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siqaATN","text_ar":"سِقَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musaAqaTapN","text_ar":"مُسَاقَطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He discoursed with him alternately;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"discourse fell"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saqaTa","text_ar":"سَقَطَ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from each of them to the other,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so as that one discoursed, and the other listened to him, and when he became silent, he who had been silent discoursed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he discoursed to him telling him thing after thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna yusaAqiTu *`lika Eano rasuwli A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"كَانَ يُسَاقِطُ ذٰلِكَ عَنْ رَسُولِ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He used to relate that from the Apostle of God amid his discourse;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though he mixed his discourse therewith. (TA, from a trad.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sAqT Alfarasu","text_ar":"ساقط الفَرَسُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEadowa","text_ar":"العَدْوَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siqaATN","text_ar":"سِقَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The horse came"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"running"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a slack,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"languid, manner:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * M, K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siqaATN","text_ar":"سِقَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a horse is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"incessantly having the foot wounded and made to bleed by stones,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hurt thereby."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) You say also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farasN ray~vu AlsiqaATi","text_ar":"فَرَسٌ رَيّثُ السِقَاطِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A horse slow in running."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sAqT Alr~ajulu","text_ar":"ساقط الرَّجُلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siqaATN","text_ar":"سِقَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The man failed of attaining to the condition of the generous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"noble."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","K","TA","A"]},{"entry_id":"n20097","headword_ar":"سَاقِطَةٌ","root":"sqT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", and its pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawaAqiTu","text_ar":"سَوَاقِطُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAqiTN","text_ar":"سَاقِطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", throughout."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}